\c 17
\cl Luke 17
\cd Lessons of avoiding scandal; of the efficacy of faith, etc. The ten lepers. The manner of the coming of Christ.
\p
\v 1 And *he said to his disciples: It is impossible that scandals should not come: but wo to him through whom they come.
\p
\v 2 It were better for him that a millstone were put about his neck, and he cast into the sea, than that he should scandalize one of these little ones.
\p
\v 3 Take heed to yourselves. *If thy brother sin against thee, reprove him: and if he do penance, forgive him.
\p
\v 4 And if he sin against thee seven times in a day, and seven times in a day turn again to thee, saying: I repent: forgive him.
\p
\v 5 And the apostles said to the Lord; Increase our faith.
\p
\v 6 *And the Lord said; If you had faith like to a grain of mustard-seed, you might say to this mulberry-tree; Be thou rooted up, and be transplanted into the sea, and it shall obey you.
\p
\v 7 But which of you having a servant ploughing or feeding cattle, will say to him when he is come from the field: Immediately go, sit down to table:
\p
\v 8 And will not rather say to him: Make ready my supper, and gird thyself, and serve me whilst I eat and drink, and afterwards thou shalt eat and drink?
\p
\v 9 Doth he thank that servant, because he did the things which he commanded him?
\p
\v 10 I think not. So you also, when you shall have done all the things that are commanded you, say: We are unprofitable servants: we have done that which we ought to do.
\p
\v 11 And it came to pass, as he was going to Jerusalem, that he passed through the midst of Samaria and Galilee.
\p
\v 12 And as he entered into a certain town, there met him ten men, that were lepers, who stood afar off:
\p
\v 13 And they lifted up their voice, saying: Jesus, master, have mercy on us.
\p
\v 14 And when he saw them, he said: *Go, shew yourselves to the priests. And it came to pass, that as they went, they were cleansed.
\p
\v 15 And one of them, when he saw that he was cleansed, went back, with a loud voice, glorifying God.
\p
\v 16 And he fell on his face before his feet, giving thanks: and this man was a Samaritan.
\p
\v 17 And Jesus answering, said, Were there not ten made clean? and where are the nine?
\p
\v 18 There is no one found to return and give glory to God, but this stranger.
\p
\v 19 And he said to him: Arise, go thy way: for thy faith hath made thee whole.
\p
\v 20 And being asked by the Pharisees, when the kingdom of God should come? he, answering them, said: The kingdom of God cometh not with observation.
\p
\v 21 Neither shall they say: Behold here, or behold there: for, lo, the kingdom of God is within you.
\p
\v 22 And he said to his disciples: The days will come, when you shall desire to see one day of the Son of man, and you shall not see it.
\p
\v 23 *And they will say to you: Lo here, and lo there. Go ye not after, nor follow them:
\p
\v 24 For as the lightening that lighteneth from under heaven, shineth unto the parts that are under heaven, so shall the Son of man be in his day.
\p
\v 25 But first he must suffer many things, and be rejected by this generation.
\p
\v 26 *And as it was in the days of Noe, so shall it be also in the days of the Son of man.
\p
\v 27 They did eat and drink, they married wives, and were given in marriage, until the day that Noe entered into the ark: and the flood came, and destroyed them all.
\p
\v 28 *Likewise, as it was in the days of Lot: They did eat and drink, they bought and sold, they planted and built:
\p
\v 29 And in the day that Lot went out of Sodom, it rained fire and brimstone from heaven, and destroyed them all:
\p
\v 30 Even thus shall it be in the day when the Son of man shall be revealed.
\p
\v 31 In that hour he that shall be on the house top, and his goods in the house, let him not go down to take them away: and he that shall be in the field, in like manner, let him not return back.
\p
\v 32 Remember Lot's wife.
\p
\v 33 *Whosoever shall seek to save his life, shall lose it: and whosoever shall lose it, shall preserve it.
\p
\v 34 I say to you: *in that night there shall be two men in one bed: the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.
\p
\v 35 Two women shall be grinding together; the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left: two men shall be in the field; the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.
\p
\v 36 They answering, said to him: Where, Lord?
\p
\v 37 He said to them: Wheresoever the body shall be, thither will the eagles also be gathered together.
